Governors on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC), have described the death of Senator Abiola Ajimobi as a huge loss to the progressives community. Mourning Ajimobi who was a two term former governor of Oyo state on the APC platform, The Progressives Governors while mourning his death added that the party will greatly miss the wealth and political experience of a great politician who selflessly sacrificed for APC. This was contained in a statement released by the Governor of Kebbi state, Atiku Bagudu on behalf of the PGF. “We received the death of His Excellency, Sen. Abiola Ajimobi with heavy heart and gratitude to Allah (SWT) for a life well blessed. “We, the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF), join the family, people and government of Oyo State and the nation to pray for the repose of the soul of our dear and beloved Sen. Abiola Ajimobi. “His death is a loss to the nation and the Nigerian progressive community. “We pray to God Almighty to grant the family the fortitude to bear this heavy loss. “May Allah reward all the good work of Sen. Ajimobi, forgive his limitations and bless what he left behind. May the soul of Sen. Abiola Ajimobi rest in peace!”, the statement read.